com.inrix.sdk

Class AlertsManager.RouteAlertCallback

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.inrix.sdk.AlertsManager.RouteAlertCallback
  • Enclosing class:
    AlertsManager

    public static class AlertsManager.RouteAlertCallback
extends Object
    This class is the contract between RouteAlert and your application. This implements all methods but does nothing. A convenience class to extend when you only want to listen for a subset of all the route alert notifications.
    See Also:
    AlertsManager.createRouteAlert(com.inrix.sdk.AlertsManager.RouteAlertOptions, com.inrix.sdk.AlertsManager.RouteAlertCallback)

      • onRouteStatus

        public void onRouteStatus(AlertsManager.OnRouteStatus routeStatus,
                 GeoPoint currentLocation,
                 double distanceRemaining)
        Callback for route status updates.
        Parameters:
        routeStatus - The route status as defined in AlertsManager.OnRouteStatus.
        currentLocation - The current location on the route, an instance of GeoPoint, the value will be the closest point on the route within the route threshold otherwise just return the current location.
        distanceRemaining - The distance remaining along the route. The units of this value are based off of UserPreferences.getSettingUnits(). The value may be -1 if unknown as in the AlertsManager.OnRouteStatus.OFF_ROUTE case.

      • onUpdatedRouteResults

        public void onUpdatedRouteResults(UpdatedRouteResults updatedRouteResults)
        Method that will be called when updated routes are successfully requested from a tracked route. This response will contain the better route if better routes are enabled. This is similar to RouteManager.IUpdatedRouteListener.
        Parameters:
        updatedRouteResults - The results.

      • onUpdatedRouteResults

        public void onUpdatedRouteResults(List<Route> routes)
        Method that will be called when the the list of routes that should be collectively updated are successfully updated. The number of routes in the result should be match the number of routes that were being updated. Each individual routes updated should have the same route id as the corresponding route in the results.
        Parameters:
        routes - The results.
